</table>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Broadcasts">Broadcasts</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Scandal_(TV_series)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Broadcasts">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>In the United States <i>Scandal</i> airs on ABC on Thursday nights at 10pm/9pm CT. The program airs at the same time in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a> through the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/City_(TV_network)" title="City (TV network)">City</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Television_system" title="Television system">television system</a> with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simultaneous_substitution" title="Simultaneous substitution">simsubbing</a> of the ABC feed.</p>
<p>The series airs on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seven_Network" title="Seven Network">Seven Network</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia" title="Australia">Australia</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canal_Sony" title="Canal Sony" class="mw-redirect">Canal Sony</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_America" title="Latin America">Latin America</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ZFB-TV" title="ZFB-TV">ZFB-TV</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bermuda" title="Bermuda">Bermuda</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miami" title="Miami">Miami</a>'s <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WPLG" title="WPLG">WPLG</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bahamas" title="Bahamas" class="mw-redirect">Bahamas</a> (via cable from the United States mainland), <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TVB_Pearl" title="TVB Pearl">TVB Pearl</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong" title="Hong Kong">Hong Kong</a>, and on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Channel_4_(UK)" title="Channel 4 (UK)" class="mw-redirect">Channel 4</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-30" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-30"><span>[</span>30<span>]</span></a></sup> It airs in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa" title="South Africa">South Africa</a> on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M-net" title="M-net" class="mw-redirect">M-net</a> titled <i>The Fixer</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-31" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-31"><span>[</span>31<span>]</span></a></sup> In <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Zealand" title="New Zealand">New Zealand</a> it first aired on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TV_One_(New_Zealand)" title="TV One (New Zealand)">TV One</a> but now airs on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TV2_(New_Zealand)" title="TV2 (New Zealand)">TV2</a>.</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Cable_syndication">Cable syndication</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Scandal_(TV_series)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Cable syndication">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>On July 15, 2013, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Entertainment_Television" title="Black Entertainment Television" class="mw-redirect">BET</a> and ABC announced an early syndication agreement which will see BET carrying a marathon of the first two seasons on August 10 and 17, 2013, then in two-hour blocks on Wednesdays before the show's season three premiere on October 3.<sup id="cite_ref-32" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-32"><span>[</span>32<span>]</span></a></sup> BET will then air new season three episodes after an eight day delay, similar to how <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fox_Broadcasting_Company" title="Fox Broadcasting Company">Fox</a> allows <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adult_swim" title="Adult swim" class="mw-redirect">adult swim</a> to air new episodes of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seth_MacFarlane" title="Seth MacFarlane">Seth MacFarlane</a>'s animated series <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Family_Guy" title="Family Guy">Family Guy</a> on a two-week delay after their network premieres.<sup id="cite_ref-33" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-33"><span>[</span>33<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34"><span>[</span>34<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
